  <chapter number="1" style="c" sid="ACT 1" />
  <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 1:1" />Indeed the first account I_made concerning all <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, oh Theofilos, of_which <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> began both to_be_doing and to_be_teaching, <verse eid="ACT 1:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 1:2" />until which day having_commanded by <char style="add">+the</char>_ holy _<char style="nd">spirit</char> to_the ambassadors, whom he_chose, he_was_taken_up, <verse eid="ACT 1:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 1:3" />to_whom also after the <char style="add">time</char> him to_suffer he_presented himself living, with many proofs through forty days, appearing to_them, and speaking the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning the kingdom of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 1:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 1:4" />And assembling_together, he_commanded to_them: From Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim) not to_be_being_departed, but to_be_awaiting the promise of_the father, which you_all_heard from_me. <verse eid="ACT 1:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 1:5" />Because Yōannaʸs on_one_hand immersed in_water, on_the_other_hand you_all will_be_being_immersed in <char style="add">+the</char>_ holy _<char style="nd">spirit</char>, after many not these days. <verse eid="ACT 1:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 1:6" />Therefore indeed the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_come_together, were_asking him saying: <char style="nd">master</char>, at this time, are_you_restoring the kingdom to_Israaʸl/(Yisərāʼēl)? <verse eid="ACT 1:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 1:7" />And he_said to them: It_is not of_you_all to_know times or seasons, which the father set by his own authority. <verse eid="ACT 1:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 1:8" />But you_all_will_be_receiving power, having_ The holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> _come_over on you_all, and you_all_will_be witnesses for_me, in both Hierousalaʸm, and in all Youdaia, and Samareia/(Shomərōn), and to <char style="add">+the</char>_last <char style="add">part</char> of_the earth. <verse eid="ACT 1:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 1:9" />And having_said these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, seeing them, he_was_lifted_up and <char style="add">+a</char>_cloud took_ him _up from the eyes of_them. <verse eid="ACT 1:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 1:10" />And as they_were looking_intently into the sky, him going, also see two men in white clothing, had_stood_by to_them, <verse eid="ACT 1:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 1:11" />who also said: Men, Galilaios, why you_all_have_stood looking at the sky? This <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> having_been_taken_up from you_all into heaven, thus will_be_coming which manner you_all_saw him going into heaven. <verse eid="ACT 1:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 1:12" />Then they_returned to Hierousalaʸm from <char style="add">+the</char>_mountain being_called of_Olivet, which is near Hierousalaʸm, having journey of_<char style="add">+a</char>_day_of_rest. <verse eid="ACT 1:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 1:13" />And when they_came_in, into the upper_room, they_went_uphill where they_were staying, jointly Petros and Yōannaʸs and Yakōbos/(Yaˊaqov) and Andreas, Filippos and Thōmas, Bartholomaios and Matthaios, Yakōbos of_Alfaios, and Simōn the Farisaios_zaʸlōtaʸs_<char style="add">group_member</char>, and Youdas/(Yəhūdāh) of_Yakōbos. <verse eid="ACT 1:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 1:14" />These all were persevering in_prayer with_one_accord, with <char style="add">+the</char>_women and Maria/(Mirəyām) the mother of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char>, and the brothers of_him. <verse eid="ACT 1:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 1:15" />And in these days, Petros having_stood_up in <char style="add">+the</char>_midst of_the brothers said (and <char style="add">+the</char>_crowd of_names with the same was about <char style="add">+a</char>_hundred twenty), <verse eid="ACT 1:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 1:16" />Men, brothers, it_was_fitting the scripture to_be_fulfilled, which the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> previously_said by <char style="add">+the</char>_mouth of_Dawid/(Dāvid) concerning Youdas, the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_become guide to_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_captured <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char>. <verse eid="ACT 1:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 1:17" />Because he_was having_been_numbered with us, and obtained <char style="add">+a</char>_lot of_ this _service. <verse eid="ACT 1:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 1:18" />(Therefore indeed this <char style="add">man</char> acquired <char style="add">+a</char>_field out_of <char style="add">+the</char>_reward of_unrighteousness, and having_become headlong, he_burst_open in_<char style="add">+the</char>_middle, and all the intestines of_him was_poured_out. <verse eid="ACT 1:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 1:19" />And it_became known to_all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> dwelling_in Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim), so_that that field to_be_called in_their language of_them, Akeldama, this is: field of_blood.) <verse eid="ACT 1:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 1:20" />For it_has_been_written in scroll of_psalms, the <char style="add">+the</char>_homestead of_him Let_be_become desolate, and let_ not _be the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> dwelling in it, and: let_ another _take The overseeing of_him. <verse eid="ACT 1:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 1:21" />Therefore it_is_fitting of_the men having_come_together with_us, at all <char style="add">+the</char>_time that the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> came_in and came_out with us, <verse eid="ACT 1:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 1:22" />having_begun from the immersion of_Yōannaʸs until the day in_which he_was_taken_up from us, <char style="add">+a</char>_witness of_the resurrection of_him with us, to_become one of_these. <verse eid="ACT 1:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 1:23" />And they_set two, Yōsaʸf/(Yōşēf) being_called Barsabbas, who was_called Youstos, and Matthias. <verse eid="ACT 1:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 1:24" />And having_prayed, they_said: You <char style="nd">master</char>, heart_knower of_all, reveal which one you_chose of these two, <verse eid="ACT 1:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 1:25" />to_take the this place of_service and commission, from which Youdas broke_from, to_be_gone to his own place. <verse eid="ACT 1:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 1:26" />And they_gave lots to_them, and the lot fell on Matthias, and he_was_chosen_together_with with the eleven ambassadors.<chapter eid="ACT 1" /><chapter number="2" style="c" sid="ACT 2" /><verse eid="ACT 1:26" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 2:1" />And at the <char style="add">time</char> the day of_pentecost to_be_being_fulfilled, they_were all together in the same <char style="add">place</char>. <verse eid="ACT 2:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 2:2" />And suddenly <char style="add">+a</char>_sound became out_of heaven, as being_carried of_<char style="add">+a</char>_ forceful _wind, and it_filled all the house where they_were sitting. <verse eid="ACT 2:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 2:3" />And dividing tongues as_if of_fire were_seen to_them, and sat_down on each one of_them. <verse eid="ACT 2:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 2:4" />And they_were_ all _filled with_<char style="add">+the</char>_ holy _<char style="nd">spirit</char>, and they_began to_be_speaking with_other tongues, as the <char style="nd">spirit</char> was_giving to_them to_be_speaking_out. <verse eid="ACT 2:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 2:5" />And Youdaiōns were dwelling in Hierousalaʸm, devout men from every nation of_the <char style="add">nations</char> under heaven. <verse eid="ACT 2:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 2:6" />And of_ this _sound having_become, the multitude came_together and was_confounded, because each one heard speaking of_them in_his. own language. <verse eid="ACT 2:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 2:7" />And they_were_amazed and they_were_marvelling saying: Behold are not, all these who <char style="add">=are</char> speaking Galilaios? <verse eid="ACT 2:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 2:8" />And how are_ we _hearing each in_the own language of_us, in which we_were_born? <verse eid="ACT 2:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 2:9" /><char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Parthia, and <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Maʸdia, and <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Elam, and the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> dwelling_in Mesopotamia, Youdaia and jointly Kappadokia, Pontos and Asia, <verse eid="ACT 2:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 2:10" />Frugia and jointly Pamfulia, Aiguptos/(Miʦərayim), and the parts of_Libuaʸ along Kuraʸnaʸ, and the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> Ɽōmaios visiting, <verse eid="ACT 2:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 2:11" />both Youdaiōns and converts, <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Kraʸtaʸ and <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Arabia, we_are_hearing them speaking, the great <char style="add">&gt;things</char> of_<char style="nd">god</char> in_our tongues. <verse eid="ACT 2:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 2:12" />And all were_marvelling and were_thoroughly_perplexed, another saying to another: What is_wanting this to_be? <verse eid="ACT 2:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 2:13" />But others mocking were_saying, They_are having_been_filled of_sweet_wine. <verse eid="ACT 2:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 2:14" />But Petros having_been_stood with the eleven, lifted_up the voice of_him and spoke_out to_them: Men, <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Youdaia, and all you_all dwelling_in Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim), let_ this _be known to_you_all and give_ear to_the messages of_me. <verse eid="ACT 2:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 2:15" />For these are_ not _being_drunk as you_all are_supposing, for it_is <char style="add">+the</char>_ third _hour, of_the day, <verse eid="ACT 2:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 2:16" />but this is the <char style="add">message</char> having_been_spoken by the prophet Yōaʸl/(Yōʼēl): <verse eid="ACT 2:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 2:17" />And it_will_be with these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> in the last days, <char style="nd">god</char> is_saying: I_will_be_pouring_out of the <char style="nd">spirit</char> of_me on all flesh, and the sons of_you_all will_be_prophesying, and the daughters of_you_all, and the young_men of_you_all will_be_seeing visions, and the elders of_you_all in_dreams will_be_being_dreamt, <verse eid="ACT 2:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 2:18" />and surely I_will_be_pouring_out of the <char style="nd">spirit</char> of_me on the slaves of_me, and on the handmaidens of_me, in those days, and they_will_be_prophesying. <verse eid="ACT 2:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 2:19" />And I_will_be_giving wonders in the sky above, and signs on the earth below, blood, and fire, and vapor of_smoke. <verse eid="ACT 2:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 2:20" />The sun will_be_being_altered into darkness and the moon into blood, before <char style="add">+the</char>_ great and glorious _day of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> to_come. <verse eid="ACT 2:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 2:21" />And it_will_be, everyone who may_call on_the name of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> will_be_being_saved. <verse eid="ACT 2:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 2:22" />Men, <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Israaʸl/(Yisərāʼēl), hear messages these: <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> the from_Nazaret, <char style="add">+a</char>_man having_been_demonstrated by <char style="nd">god</char> to you_all by_miracles, and wonders, and signs, which <char style="nd">god</char> did by him in <char style="add">+the</char>_midst of_you_all, as you_all_ yourselves _have_known. <verse eid="ACT 2:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 2:23" />This <char style="add">man</char> by_the, having_been_designated counsel and foreknowledge of_<char style="nd">god</char>, delivered_up by <char style="add">+the</char>_hand of_<char style="add">+the</char>_lawless <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>, you_all_killed having_executed_on_a_stake. <verse eid="ACT 2:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 2:24" />Whom <char style="nd">god</char> raised_up, having_untied/released the agonies of_the death, as_much_as was not possible him to_be_being_restrained by it. <verse eid="ACT 2:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 2:25" />For Dawid/(Dāvid) is_saying to him: I_was_foreseeing the <char style="nd">master</char> before me through all <char style="add">time</char>, because he_is on <char style="add">+the</char>_right <char style="add">hand</char> of_me, in_order_that I _may_ not _be_shaken. <verse eid="ACT 2:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 2:26" />Because_of this the heart of_me was_gladdened, and the tongue of_me exulted, and still also the flesh of_me will_be_nesting in hope, <verse eid="ACT 2:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 2:27" />because you will_ not _be_abandoning the soul of_me into Hadaʸs, nor will_you_be_giving the devout <char style="add">&gt;one</char> of_you to_see decay. <verse eid="ACT 2:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 2:28" />You_made_known to_me <char style="add">+the</char>_ways of_life, you_will_be_filling me with_gladness with the presence of_you. <verse eid="ACT 2:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 2:29" />Men, brothers, it_is_permitting to_speak with confidence to you_all concerning the patriarch Dawid that he_ both _died and was_buried, and the tomb of_him is among us until this day. <verse eid="ACT 2:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 2:30" />Therefore being <char style="add">+a</char>_prophet, and having_known that <char style="nd">god</char> swore to_him with_<char style="add">+an</char>_oath: of <char style="add">+the</char>_fruit of_the loin of_him, to_sit_down on the throne of_him. <verse eid="ACT 2:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 2:31" />Having_foreseen, he_spoke concerning the resurrection of_the <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> that neither was_abandoned into Hadaʸs, nor the flesh of_him saw decay. <verse eid="ACT 2:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 2:32" />This <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">god</char> raised_up, of_which all we are witnesses. <verse eid="ACT 2:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 2:33" />Therefore having_been_exalted by_the right <char style="add">hand</char> of_<char style="nd">god</char>, and having_received the promise of_the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char>, from the father, he_poured_ this _out which you_all are_seeing and are_hearing. <verse eid="ACT 2:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 2:34" />For Dawid not went_up into the heavens, but himself is_saying, <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> Said to_the <char style="nd">master</char> of_me: Be_sitting on <char style="add">+the</char>_right <char style="add">hand</char> of_me, <verse eid="ACT 2:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 2:35" />until I_may_put the enemies of_you <char style="add">+a</char>_footstool of_the feet of_you. <verse eid="ACT 2:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 2:36" />Assuredly therefore let_ All <char style="add">+the</char>_house of_Israaʸl/(Yisərāʼēl) _be_knowing that <char style="nd">god</char> made him both <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char> and <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, this <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> whom you_all executed_on_a_stake. <verse eid="ACT 2:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 2:37" />And having_heard, they_were_pierced to_the heart, and they_said to Petros and the other ambassadors: What may_we_do, men, brothers? <verse eid="ACT 2:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 2:38" />And Petros is_saying to them: Repent: and let_ each of_you_all _be_immersed in the name of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one</char>, for forgiveness of_the sins of_you_all, and you_all_will_be_receiving the gift of_the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char>. <verse eid="ACT 2:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 2:39" />For the promise is to_you_all, and to_the children of_you_all, and to_all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> at far, as_many_as may_call_to <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">master</char>, the <char style="nd">god</char> of_us. <verse eid="ACT 2:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 2:40" />Both with_ more _other messages he_testified, and was_exhorting them saying: Be_saved from this crooked generation. <verse eid="ACT 2:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="ACT 2:41" />Therefore indeed the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_welcomed the message of_him were_immersed, and were_added on that day, about three_thousand souls. <verse eid="ACT 2:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="ACT 2:42" />And they_were persevering in_the teaching of_the ambassadors, and in_fellowship, the breaking of_the bread, and in_prayers. <verse eid="ACT 2:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="ACT 2:43" />And reverence was_becoming on_every soul, and many wonders and signs was_becoming through the ambassadors. in Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim). and great fear was with all. <verse eid="ACT 2:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="ACT 2:44" />and And all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_believed were with the same <char style="add">purpose</char>, and they_were_having all common <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, <verse eid="ACT 2:44" /><verse number="45" style="v" sid="ACT 2:45" />and they_were_selling their properties and their possessions, and they_were_dividing them to_all, anyone was_having as_much_as would need. <verse eid="ACT 2:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="ACT 2:46" />And in_every day persevering with_one_accord in the temple, and breaking bread in_every house, they_were_partaking of_food with exultation and simplicity of_heart, <verse eid="ACT 2:46" /><verse number="47" style="v" sid="ACT 2:47" />praising <char style="nd">god</char> and having favour with all the people. And the <char style="nd">master</char> was_adding the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being_saved with the same. in_every day.<chapter eid="ACT 2" /><chapter number="3" style="c" sid="ACT 3" /><verse eid="ACT 2:47" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 3:1" />And Petros also Yōannaʸs were_going_uphill into the temple at the hour of_prayer the ninth <char style="add">hour</char>. <verse eid="ACT 3:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 3:2" />And <char style="add">+a</char>_certain man, being lame from <char style="add">+the</char>_womb of_<char style="add">+the</char>_mother of_him, was_being_born, whom they_were_putting in_every day at the door of_the temple, being_called Beautiful, to_be_requesting alms from the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> entering_in into the temple. <verse eid="ACT 3:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 3:3" />Who having_seen Petros and Yōannaʸs going to_be_entering into the temple, was_asking to_receive alms. <verse eid="ACT 3:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 3:4" />But Petros having_looked_intently at him with Yōannaʸs said: Look to us. <verse eid="ACT 3:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 3:5" />And he was_holding_on to_them, expecting to_receive something from them. <verse eid="ACT 3:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 3:6" />But Petros said: Silver and gold is_ not _being to_me, but this what I_am_having, I_am_giving to_you, in the name of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> of_the from_Nazaret, be_walking. <verse eid="ACT 3:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 3:7" />And having_grabbed him by_the right hand, he_raised him, and immediately the feet of_him and the ankles were_strengthened. <verse eid="ACT 3:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 3:8" />And leaping_up, he_stood and was_walking, and came_in with them into the temple, walking, and springing_up, and praising <char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 3:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 3:9" />And all the people saw him walking and praising the <char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 3:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 3:10" />And they_were_recognizing him that he was the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> sitting at the Beautiful gate of_the temple for the alms, and they_were_filled with_amazement and amazement at the <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> having_been_happened to_him. <verse eid="ACT 3:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 3:11" />And of_him taking_hold_of Petros and Yōannaʸs, all the people ran_together to them in the portico being_called of_Solomōn/(Shəlomih), greatly_amazed. <verse eid="ACT 3:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 3:12" />But Petros having_seen <char style="add">it</char>, answered to the people: Men, <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Israaʸl/(Yisərāʼēl), why you_all_are_wondering at this, or why you_all_are_looking_intently at_us, as_though by_<char style="add">^our</char>_own power or devoutness having_made him to_be_walking? <verse eid="ACT 3:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 3:13" />The <char style="nd">god</char> of_Abraʼam/(ʼAvərāhām), and the <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd">god</char> of_Isaʼak/(Yiʦəḩāq), and the <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="nd"