" />And of_them departing, they_were_imploring these messages to_be_spoken to_them on the afterward day_of_rest. <verse eid="ACT 13:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="ACT 13:43" />And having_been_released of_the synagogue, many of_the Youdaiōns and of_the worshipping converts followed after_Paulos and Barnabas, who addressing to_them, were_persuading them to_be_remaining in_the grace of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 13:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="ACT 13:44" />And on_the coming day_of_rest, almost all the city was_gathered_together to_hear the message of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 13:44" /><verse number="45" style="v" sid="ACT 13:45" />But the Youdaiōns having_seen the crowds, they_were_filled with_jealousy and they_were_speaking_against against_the_ slandering _<char style="add">&gt;things</char> being_spoken by Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 13:45" /><verse number="46" style="v" sid="ACT 13:46" />and, Paulos and Barnabas Having_spoken_boldly said, it_was necessary the message of_<char style="nd">god</char> first to_be_spoken To_you_all. Since and you_all_are_pushing_ it _away, and not worthy you_all_are_judging yourselves of_eternal life, see, we_are_being_turned to the pagans. <verse eid="ACT 13:46" /><verse number="47" style="v" sid="ACT 13:47" />For thus the <char style="nd">master</char> has_commanded to_us: I_have_set you for <char style="add">+a</char>_light of_<char style="add">+the</char>_pagans, you to_be for salvation to <char style="add">+the</char>_last of_the earth. <verse eid="ACT 13:47" /><verse number="48" style="v" sid="ACT 13:48" />And hearing <char style="add">it</char> the pagans, they_were_rejoicing and were_glorifying the message of_the <char style="nd">master</char>, and as_many_as were having_been_appointed to eternal life believed. <verse eid="ACT 13:48" /><verse number="49" style="v" sid="ACT 13:49" />And the message of_the <char style="nd">master</char> was_being_carried_through through all the r