nd having_said, I_will_be_returning to you_all Again, <char style="nd">god</char> willing, he_was_launched from Efesos. <verse eid="ACT 18:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 18:22" />And having_come_downhill to Kaisareia, having_gone_up and having_greeted the assembly, he_came_downhill to Antioⱪeia. <verse eid="ACT 18:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 18:23" />And having_worked <char style="add">+a</char>_certain time, he_came_out passing_through consecutively the Galatikos region and Frugia, strengthening all the apprentices/followers. <verse eid="ACT 18:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 18:24" />And <char style="add">+a</char>_ certain _Youdaios by_<char style="add">+the</char>_name Apollōs from_Alexandria by_descent, <char style="add">+a</char>_scholarly man, arrived to Efesos, being powerful in the scriptures. <verse eid="ACT 18:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 18:25" />This <char style="add">&gt;one</char> was having_been_instructed the way of_the <char style="nd">master</char>, and being_zealous in_spirit, he_was_speaking and was_teaching exactly the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char>, knowing only the immersion of_Yōannaʸs. <verse eid="ACT 18:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 18:26" />And this <char style="add">&gt;one</char> began to_be_speaking_boldly in the synagogue. But having_heard from_him, Priskilla and Akulas took_ him _aside, and they_explained the way of_<char style="nd">god</char> more_exactly to_him. <verse eid="ACT 18:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 18:27" />And about_him wishing to_pass_through into Aⱪaia, the brothers having_encouraged <char style="add"> him</char>, wrote to_the apprentices/followers to_welcome him, who having_arrived, contributed much to_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_believed through grace. <verse eid="ACT 18:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 18:28" />For vigorously he_was_thoroughly_refuting publicly against_the Youdaiōns, showing <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> to_be the <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> by the scriptures.<chapter eid="ACT 18" /><chapter number="19" style="c" sid="ACT 19" /><verse eid="ACT 18:28" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 19:1" />And it_became at the <char style="add">time</char>, Apollōs to_be in Korinthos, Paulos having_passed_through the upper parts, to_come_downhill to Efesos and to_find some apprentices/followers, <verse eid="ACT 19:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 19:2" />and said to them: having_believed you_all_received <char style="add">+the</char>_ holy _<char style="nd">spirit</char>? And they <char style="add">said</char> to him: But we_ not_even _heard whether there_is holy <char style="nd">spirit</char>. <verse eid="ACT 19:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 19:3" />and, he_said: Therefore into what were_you_all_immersed? And they said: Into the immersion of_Yōannaʸs. <verse eid="ACT 19:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 19:4" />And Paulos said: Yōannaʸs immersed with_<char style="add">+an</char>_immersion of_repentance, saying to_the people that they_may_believe in the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> coming after him this is in <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char>. <verse eid="ACT 19:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 19:5" />And having_heard, they_were_immersed in the name of_the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char>. <verse eid="ACT 19:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 19:6" />And of_Paulos having_laying_on on_them <char style="add">^his</char>_hands, the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> came on them, and they_were_speaking with_tongues and were_prophesying. <verse eid="ACT 19:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 19:7" />And the all were men about twelve. <verse eid="ACT 19:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 19:8" />And having_come_in into the synagogue, he_was_speaking_boldly for three months, discussing and persuading concerning the kingdom of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 19:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 19:9" />But when some were_being_hardened and were_disbelieving, speaking_evil <char style="add">of</char> the way before the multitude, having_withdrew from them he_set_apart the apprentices/followers, in_every day discussing in the school of_Turannos. <verse eid="ACT 19:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 19:10" />And this became for two years, so_that all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> dwelling_in Asia to_hear the message of_the <char style="nd">master</char>, both Youdaiōns and Hellaʸns. <verse eid="ACT 19:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 19:11" />And <char style="nd">god</char> was_doing not having_been_ordinary miracles, by the hands of_Paulos, <verse eid="ACT 19:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 19:12" />so_that even to the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> ailing handkerchiefs or aprons to_be_being_carried_away from the skin of_him, and the diseases to_be_being_released from them, and the the evil spirits to_be_going_out. <verse eid="ACT 19:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 19:13" />But some also the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> Youdaiōns exorcists going_around attempted to_be_naming over the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having the the evil spirits in_the name of_the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> saying: I_am_imploring you_all, by_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char>, whom Paulos is_proclaiming. <verse eid="ACT 19:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 19:14" />and seven sons of_one of_Skeuas Youdaiōns chief_priest Were doing this. <verse eid="ACT 19:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 19:15" />But the evil spirit answering said to_them: <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> I_am_knowing, and Paulos I_am_recognizing, but who_all are you_all? <verse eid="ACT 19:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 19:16" />And the man in whom was the evil spirit having_leapt_on, on, them, having_exercised_mastership over_both, it_prevailed against against_them, so_that to_escape out_of that house naked and having_been_wounded. <verse eid="ACT 19:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 19:17" />And this became known to_all, both to_Youdaiōns and Hellaʸns, the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> dwelling_in Efesos, and fear fell_on on all them, and the name of_the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> was_being_magnified. <verse eid="ACT 19:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 19:18" />And many of_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_believed, were_coming confessing and declaring the practices of_them. <verse eid="ACT 19:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 19:19" />And many of_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_practiced the magical, having_brought_together their scrolls, they_were_burning_up <char style="add">them</char> before all. And they_counted_up the prices of_them, and they_found five ten_thousand of_silver. <verse eid="ACT 19:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 19:20" />Thus the message of_the <char style="nd">master</char> was_growing with power and was_prevailing. <verse eid="ACT 19:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 19:21" />And when was_fulfilled these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, purposed Paulos in the <char style="nd">spirit</char>, having_passed_through Makedonia and Aⱪaia, to_be_going to Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim) having_said, After the <char style="add">time</char> to_become me there, it_is_fitting me also Ɽōmaʸ to_see. <verse eid="ACT 19:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 19:22" />And having_sent_out into Makedonia, two of_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> serving unto_him, Timotheos and Erastos, he held_on <char style="add">+a</char>_time in Asia. <verse eid="ACT 19:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 19:23" />And concerning that time, <char style="add">+a</char>_ not little _disturbance became concerning the way. <verse eid="ACT 19:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 19:24" />For <char style="add">+a</char>_certain silversmith by_<char style="add">+the</char>_name Daʸmaʸtrios, making temples silver of_Artemas, was_bringing_about no little business to_the craftsmen, <verse eid="ACT 19:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 19:25" />whom having_convened_together also the workers about such <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, he_said: Men, you_all_are_knowing that the prosperity to_us is from this business. <verse eid="ACT 19:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 19:26" />And you_all_are_observing and are_hearing that not only Efesos, but almost of_all Asia, this Paulos having_persuaded, redirected much crowd, saying that the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> by <char style="add">^our</char>_hands becoming they_are not gods. <verse eid="ACT 19:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 19:27" />But this is_ not only _risking_danger to_us, the trade to_come into disrepute, but also the temple of_the great goddess of_Artemas, to_be_reckoned for nothing, but of_the greatness of_her to_be_going also to_be_being_taken_down, whom all Asia and the inhabited_world is_worshipping. <verse eid="ACT 19:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 19:28" />And having_heard, and having_become full of_rage, they_were_crying_out saying: Great <char style="add">=is</char> Artemas of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Efesos. <verse eid="ACT 19:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 19:29" />And the city was_filled of_confusion, and they_rushed with_one_accord to the theatre, having_seized <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Makedonia Gaios and Aristarⱪos, travelling_companions of_Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 19:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 19:30" />But Paulos wishing to_come_in to the public, the apprentices/followers were_ not _allowing him. <verse eid="ACT 19:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 19:31" />And some also of_the Asian_rulers, being friends to_him, having_sent to him, they_were_imploring <char style="add"> him</char> not to_give himself into the theatre. <verse eid="ACT 19:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 19:32" />Therefore indeed others <char style="add">+a</char>_certain other <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> were_crying_out, for the assembly was having_been_confounded, and the more had_ not _known for_what on_account they_had_come_together. <verse eid="ACT 19:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 19:33" />And out_of the crowd they_concluded Alexandros, of_the Youdaiōns having_put_ him _forward. And Alexandros having_gestured his hand, was_wanting to_be_defending to_the public. <verse eid="ACT 19:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 19:34" />But having_recognized that he_is <char style="add">+a</char>_Youdaios, cry there_became one from all, over about two hours crying_out: Great Artemas of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Efesos. <verse eid="ACT 19:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 19:35" />And the clerk having_calmed the crowd is_saying: Men, <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Efesos, for who is of_<char style="add">+the</char>_people, who is_ not _knowing the city of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Efesos being temple_keeper of_the great Artemas and of_the fallen_from_Zeus <char style="add">image</char>? <verse eid="ACT 19:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 19:36" />Therefore these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> being unquestionable, it_is fitting you_all to_be_being having_been_calmed, and to_be_doing nothing reckless. <verse eid="ACT 19:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 19:37" />For you_all_brought these men, neither temple-robbers nor slandering the goddess of_us. <verse eid="ACT 19:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 19:38" />If therefore on_one_hand Daʸmaʸtrios and the craftsmen with him are_having <char style="add">+a</char>_matter against anyone, courts are_being_brought and there_are proconsuls, let_them_be_indicting against_one_another. <verse eid="ACT 19:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 19:39" />On_the_other_hand if you_all_are_seeking_after anything concerning others, it_will_be_being_settled in the lawful assembly. <verse eid="ACT 19:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 19:40" />For we_ also _are_risking_danger to_be_being_indicted of_insurrection concerning the <char style="add">day</char> today, nothing being cause, concerning which we will_ not _be_able to_give_back <char style="add">+a</char>_account concerning this disorderly_gathering. And having_said these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, he_sent_away the assembly.<chapter eid="ACT 19" /><chapter number="20" style="c" sid="ACT 20" /><verse eid="ACT 19:40" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 20:1" />And after the <char style="add">time</char> the commotion to_cease, Paulos having_sent_for the apprentices/followers and having_greeted having_exhorted, he_came_out to_be_going to Makedonia. <verse eid="ACT 20:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 20:2" />And having_passed_through those districts, and having_exhorted them with_ much _speech, he_came to Hellas. <verse eid="ACT 20:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 20:3" />And having_worked three months, <char style="add">+a</char>_plot by the Youdaiōns having_become to_him, going to_be_being_launched into Suria/(ʼArām), he_became of_<char style="add">+an</char>_opinion to_be_returning through Makedonia. <verse eid="ACT 20:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 20:4" />And Sōpatros of_Pyrrhus from_Beroia, And of_<char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Thessalonikaʸ Aristarⱪos and Sekoundos, and Gaios from_Derbaʸ, and Timotheos, And <char style="add">+the</char>_<char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Asia Tuⱪikos and Trofimos was_accompanying. with_him. <verse eid="ACT 20:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 20:5" />And these having_approached were_remaining with_us in Trōias. <verse eid="ACT 20:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 20:6" />And we sailed_away from Filippou after the days of_non-fermented <char style="add">bread</char>, and until five days came to them at Trōias, where we_stayed seven days. <verse eid="ACT 20:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 20:7" />And on the first <char style="add">day</char> of_the week, us having_been_gathered_together to_break bread, Paulos was_discussing with_them, going to_be_departing on_the <char style="add">day</char> of_next, and was_prolonging the speech until midnight. <verse eid="ACT 20:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 20:8" />And there_were many lamps in the upper_room, where we_were having_been_gathered_together. <verse eid="ACT 20:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 20:9" />And <char style="add">+a</char>_certain young_man by_<char style="add">+the</char>_name Eutuⱪos sitting by the window, being_overcome by_ deep _sleep, as_ Paulos _discussing on more, having_been_overcome by sleep, he_fell down from the third_story, and was_taken_up dead. <verse eid="ACT 20:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 20:10" />But having_come_downhill, Paulos fell_on on_him and having_embraced <char style="add"> him</char> said: Be_ not _being_distressed, for the life of_him is in him. <verse eid="ACT 20:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 20:11" />And having_gone_up, and having_broke the bread and having_tasted <char style="add">it</char>, and for having_ much _conversed until daybreak, thus he_came_out. <verse eid="ACT 20:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 20:12" />And they_brought the boy living, and were_comforted not moderately. <verse eid="ACT 20:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 20:13" />But we, having_approached to the ship, were_launched to Assos, from_there going to_be_taking_up Paulos, for thus having_been_directed, he_ himself _was going to_be_going_on_foot. <verse eid="ACT 20:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 20:14" />And when he_was_encountering with_us in Assos, having_taken_ him _up, we_came to Mitulaʸnaʸ. <verse eid="ACT 20:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 20:15" />And_from_there having_sailed_away, on_the_ following _<char style="add">day</char> we_arrived opposite Ⱪios, and on_the next <char style="add">day</char> we_arrived in Samos, and on_the_ following _<char style="add">day</char> we_came to Milaʸtos. <verse eid="ACT 20:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 20:16" />For Paulos had_judged to_sail_past Efesos, so_that may_ not _become to_him to_spend_time in Asia, for he_was_hurrying if possible it_might_be to_him, the day of_pentecost to_become in Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim). <verse eid="ACT 20:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 20:17" />And from Milaʸtos, having_sent to Efesos, he_summoned the elders of_the assembly. <verse eid="ACT 20:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 20:18" />And when they_arrived to him, he_said to_them: You_all are_knowing from <char style="add">+the</char>_first day from which I_set_foot_in in Asia, how I_became with you_all the whole time, <verse eid="ACT 20:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 20:19" />serving for_the <char style="nd">master</char> with all humility, and tears, and trials, in the plots of_the Youdaiōns having_happened, to_me, <verse eid="ACT 20:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 20:20" />how I_shrunk_back nothing of_the_ benefitting _<char style="add">&gt;things</char> to_ not _declare to_you_all, and to_teach you_all with_publicly and in <char style="add">all</char> homes, <verse eid="ACT 20:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 20:21" />testifying to_ both _Youdaiōns and to_Hellaʸns, repentance toward <char style="nd">god</char> and faith toward the <char style="nd">master</char> of_us, <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char>. <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char>. <verse eid="ACT 20:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 20:22" />And now see, I having_been_bound by_the <char style="nd">spirit</char>, am_going to Hierousalaʸm, not having_known the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> in it going_to_be_meeting with_me. <verse eid="ACT 20:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 20:23" />except that the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> in_every city is_testifying to_me, saying that bonds and tribulations are_remaining me. <verse eid="ACT 20:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 20:24" />But of_nothing account I_am_making the life precious to_myself, so_as I_may_complete the course of_me, and the service which I_received from the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char>, to_testify the good_message of_the grace of_<char style="nd">god</char>. <verse eid="ACT 20:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 20:25" />And now see, I have_known that you_all all among whom I_passed_through proclaiming the kingdom. will_ no_longer _be_seeing. the face of_me. <verse eid="ACT 20:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 20:26" />Therefore I_am_testifying to_you_all in the today day that I_am pure from the blood of_all, <verse eid="ACT 20:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 20:27" />for I_ not _shrunk_back to_ not _declare all the counsel of_<char style="nd">god</char> to_you_all. <verse eid="ACT 20:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 20:28" />Be_taking_heed to_yourselves and to_all the flock, among which the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> set you_all overseers, to_be_shepherding the assembly of_the of_<char style="nd">god</char>, which he_procured through his his own blood. <verse eid="ACT 20:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 20:29" />I have_known that after the departure of_me heavy wolves will_be_coming_in among you_all, not sparing from_the flock, <verse eid="ACT 20:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 20:30" />and from of_you_all yourselves men will_be_rising_up speaking having_been_perverted <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, of_the <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> to_be_drawing_out apprentices/followers after themselves. <verse eid="ACT 20:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 20:31" />Therefore be_watching, remembering that night and day for_three_year, I_ not _ceased admonishing each one with tears. <verse eid="ACT 20:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 20:32" />And now the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> I_am_entrusting you_all to_<char style="nd">god</char>, and to_the message of_the grace of_him, being_able to_build and to_give the <char style="add">+an</char>_inheritance among all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_been_sanctified. <verse eid="ACT 20:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 20:33" />I_coveted of_silver, or gold, or clothing, of_no_one. <verse eid="ACT 20:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 20:34" />you_all_ yourselves _are_knowing that these hands attended to_the needs of_me and to_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being with me. <verse eid="ACT 20:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 20:35" />all <char style="add">&gt;things</char> I_showed to_you_all that thus laboring it_is_fitting to_be_taking_care of_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> faltering, and to_be_remembering about_the messages of_the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> that he said: it_is more Blessed, to_be_giving than to_be_receiving. <verse eid="ACT 20:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 20:36" />And having_said these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, having_knelt the knees of_him, he_prayed with them all. <verse eid="ACT 20:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 20:37" />And much weeping became of_all, and having_embraced on the neck of_Paulos, they_were_kissing him, <verse eid="ACT 20:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 20:38" />distressing most_of_all for the message which he_had_spoken that they_are_ no_longer _going to_be_observing the face of_him. And they_were_accompanying him to the ship.<chapter eid="ACT 20" /><chapter number="21" style="c" sid="ACT 21" /><verse eid="ACT 20:38" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 21:1" />And when it_became us to_be_launched, having_been_withdrawn from them, having_run_straight we_came to Kōs, and on_the_ next _<char style="add">day</char> to Ɽodos, and_from_there to Patara. <verse eid="ACT 21:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 21:2" />And having_found <char style="add">+a</char>_ship stakeing_over into Foinikaʸ, having_boarded we_were_launched. <verse eid="ACT 21:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 21:3" />And Kupros having_appeared, and having_left it on_<char style="add">+the</char>_left, we_were_sailing to Suria/(ʼArām) and we_came_downhill at Turos/(Tsor), for there the ship was unloading the cargo. <verse eid="ACT 21:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 21:4" />And having_sought_out the apprentices/followers, we_remained_on there seven days, who were_saying by the <char style="nd">spirit</char> to_Paulos not to_be_setting_foot_in to Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim). <verse eid="ACT 21:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 21:5" />And when it_became to_us to_finish_out the days, having_come_out we_were_journeying, wives and children accompanying with us all, as_far_as outside the city, and having_knelt the knees on the shore having_prayed, <verse eid="ACT 21:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 21:6" />we_withdrew from_one_another and we_went_uphill into the ship, and those returned to their own <char style="add">homes</char>. <verse eid="ACT 21:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 21:7" />And we, having_completed the voyage from Turos, arrived to Ptolemais, and having_greeted the brothers, we_remained one day with them. <verse eid="ACT 21:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 21:8" />And on_the <char style="add">day</char> of_next, having_come_out we_came to Kaisareia, and having_come_in into the house of_Filippos, the good_message_preacher, being of the seven, we_remained with him. <verse eid="ACT 21:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 21:9" />And with_this <char style="add">man</char> were four daughters, virgins prophesying. <verse eid="ACT 21:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 21:10" />And remaining_on more days, <char style="add">+a</char>_certain prophet by_<char style="add">+the</char>_name Agabos came_downhill from Youdaia, <verse eid="ACT 21:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 21:11" />and having_come to us, and having_taken_up the belt of_Paulos, having_bound of_himself the feet and the hands, he_said: The holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> is_saying these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>: The man of_whom is this belt, thus the Youdaiōns in Hierousalaʸm will_be_binding, and they_will_be_giving_over <char style="add"> him</char> into <char style="add">+the</char>_hands of_<char style="add">+the</char>_pagans. <verse eid="ACT 21:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 21:12" />And when we_heard these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, both we and the of_<char style="add">+the</char>_locals were_imploring, him not to_be_going_uphill to Hierousalaʸm. <verse eid="ACT 21:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 21:13" />Then Paulos answered: What are_you_all_doing, weeping and breaking the heart of_me? For I I_am_having ready not only to_be_bound, but also to_die_off in Hierousalaʸm, for the name of_the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char>. <verse eid="ACT 21:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 21:14" />And him not being_persuaded, we_kept_quiet having_said: The will of_the <char style="nd">master</char> let_be_becoming. <verse eid="ACT 21:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 21:15" />And after these days, having_made_preparations, we_were_going_uphill to Hierousalaʸm. <verse eid="ACT 21:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 21:16" />And also of_the apprentices/followers from Kaisareia came_together with us, bringing <char style="add">us</char> to_Mnasōn <char style="add">+a</char>_certain ancient from_Kupros apprentice/follower with whom we_may_be_lodged. <verse eid="ACT 21:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 21:17" />And of_us having_become at Hierousalaʸm, the brothers gladly welcomed us. <verse eid="ACT 21:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 21:18" />and on_the <char style="add">day</char> following, Paulos was_entering with us to Yakōbos/(Yaˊaqov), and all the elders arrived. <verse eid="ACT 21:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 21:19" />And having_greeted them, he_was_explaining by each one, of_what <char style="nd">god</char> did among the pagans by the service of_him. <verse eid="ACT 21:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 21:20" />And they having_heard were_glorifying <char style="nd">god</char>, and they_said to_him: You_are_observing, brother, how_many tens_of_thousands are among the Youdaiōns having_believed, and they_are_ all _being zealous for_the law. <verse eid="ACT 21:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 21:21" />And they_were_instructed concerning you, that you_are_teaching apostasy from Mōsaʸs/(Mosheh) all Youdaiōns the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> among the pagans, saying them not to_be_circumcising their children, nor to_be_walking in_the customs. <verse eid="ACT 21:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 21:22" />Therefore what is_it? Certainly they_will_be_hearing that you_have_come. <verse eid="ACT 21:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 21:23" />Therefore do this, what we_are_saying to_you. Four Men are with_us, having <char style="add">+a</char>_vow for themselves. <verse eid="ACT 21:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 21:24" />Having_taken these <char style="add">men</char>, be_purified with them and spend for them, in_order_that they_will_be_shaving his head, and all will_be_knowing that of_which they_have_been_instructed about you nothing is, but you_are_aligning also yourself, keeping the law. <verse eid="ACT 21:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 21:25" />But concerning the pagans having_believed, we sent_out having_judged them to_be_keeping, from_the jointly idol_sacrificed <char style="add">&gt;thing</char>, and blood, and strangled <char style="add">animals</char>, and sexual_immorality. <verse eid="ACT 21:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 21:26" />Then Paulos having_taken the men, on_the following day with them having_been_purified, was_entering into the temple, proclaiming the fulfillment of_the days of_the purification, until of_which the offering was_offered for each one of_them. <verse eid="ACT 21:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 21:27" />And when the seven days were_going, to_be_being_completed, the Youdaiōns from Asia, having_seen him in the temple, were_confounding all the crowd, and they_laid_on their hands on him <verse eid="ACT 21:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 21:28" />crying_out: Men, <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>_from_Israaʸl/(Yisərāʼēl), be_giving_help. This is the man, who teaching all everywhere against the people, and the law, and this place, and still also brought_in Hellaʸns into the temple, and has_defiled this holy place. <verse eid="ACT 21:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 21:29" />For they_were having_previously_seen Trofimos the from_Efesos in the city with him, whom they_were_thinking that Paulos brought_in into the temple. <verse eid="ACT 21:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 21:30" />And the whole city was_stirred, and <char style="add">+a</char>_rushing_together of_the people became, and having_taken_hold of_Paulos, they_were_dragging him outside the temple, and immediately the doors were_shut. <verse eid="ACT 21:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 21:31" />and seeking to_kill_ him _off, there_went_uphill <char style="add">+an</char>_allegation to_the commander of_the cohort, that all Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim) is_being_confounded, <verse eid="ACT 21:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 21:32" />who immediately having_taken soldiers and centurions, ran_down on them, and having_seen the commander and the soldiers, they_ceased striking Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 21:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 21:33" />Then having_neared, the commander took_hold of_him, and commanded <char style="add"> him</char> to_be_bound with_ two _chains, and he_was_inquiring who he_might_be and what he_is having_done. <verse eid="ACT 21:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 21:34" />But others, were_crying_out some other <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> in the crowd. And him not of_being_able to_know the certain <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> because_of the commotion, he_commanded him to_be_being_brought into the barracks. <verse eid="ACT 21:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 21:35" />And when he_became to the stairs, it_happened him to_be_being_borne by the soldiers, because_of the force of_the crowd. <verse eid="ACT 21:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 21:36" />For the multitude of_the people was_following crying_out: Be_Taking_ him _away. <verse eid="ACT 21:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 21:37" />And going to_be_being_brought_in into the barracks, Paulos is_saying to_the commander: is_it_permitting to_me to_say something to you? And he was_saying: You_are_knowing In_Hellaʸn? <verse eid="ACT 21:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 21:38" />Consequently are you not the from_Aiguptos/(Miʦərayim), who before these days, having_upset and having_led_out the four_thousand men of_the assassins into the wilderness? <verse eid="ACT 21:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 21:39" />But Paulos said: On_one_hand I am <char style="add">+a</char>_Youdaiōns <char style="add">+a</char>_man, from_Tarsos, of_Kilikia, <char style="add">+a</char>_citizen of_<char style="add">+an</char>_ not _insignificant city. On_the_other_hand I_am_beseeching of_you, permit to_me to_speak to the people. <verse eid="ACT 21:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 21:40" />And of_ him _having_permitted, Paulos having_stood on the stairs, gestured with_his hand to_the people, and great silence having_become, he_called_out in_his Hebraios language saying,<chapter eid="ACT 21" /><chapter number="22" style="c" sid="ACT 22" /><verse eid="ACT 21:40" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 22:1" />Men, brothers, and fathers, hear to you_all now of_<char style="add">+the</char>_defense of_me. <verse eid="ACT 22:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 22:2" />(And having_heard that he_was_calling_out to_them in_the Hebraios language, they_brought_about more quietness.) And he_is_saying: <verse eid="ACT 22:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 22:3" />I am <char style="add">+a</char>_ Youdaiōns _man, having_been_born in Tarsos of_Kilikia, but having_been_brought_up in this city, before the feet of_Gamaliaʸl/(Gaməlīʼēl), having_been_instructed according_to <char style="add">+the</char>_exactness of_our ancestral law, being zealous for_<char style="nd">god</char>, as all you_all are today, <verse eid="ACT 22:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 22:4" />who I_persecuted this way until death, binding and giving_over to prisons, both men and women, <verse eid="ACT 22:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 22:5" />as also the chief_priest was_testifying to_me and all the council_of_elders, from whom also having_received letters to the brothers, I_was_going to Damaskos/(Dammeseq), going_to_ also _bring the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being there, having_been_bound to Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim), in_order_that they_may_be_punished. <verse eid="ACT 22:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 22:6" />But it_became to_me journeying, and nearing to_Damaskos about midday, suddenly much light from the sky to_flash_around around me. <verse eid="ACT 22:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 22:7" />And I_fell to the ground, and I_heard of_<char style="add">+a</char>_voice saying to_me: Saulos/(Shāʼūl), Saulos, why are_you_persecuting me? <verse eid="ACT 22:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 22:8" />And I answered: Who are_you, master? And he_said to me: I am <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> the from_Nazaret, whom you are_persecuting. <verse eid="ACT 22:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 22:9" />And the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being with me, on_one_hand they_saw the light, on_the_other_hand they_ not _heard the voice of_the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> speaking to_me. <verse eid="ACT 22:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 22:10" />And I_said What may_I_do, <char style="nd">master</char>? And the <char style="nd">master</char> said to me: Having_risen_up be_going to Damaskos, and_there will_be_being_spoken to_you concerning all <char style="add">&gt;things</char> that has_been_determined for_you to_do. <verse eid="ACT 22:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 22:11" />But as I_was_ not _focusing_in because_of the glory of_that light, being_led_by_hand by the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being_with with_me, I_came to Damaskos. <verse eid="ACT 22:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 22:12" />And Ananias <char style="add">+a</char>_certain devout man according_to the law, being_attested by all the Youdaiōns dwelling <char style="add">there</char>, <verse eid="ACT 22:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 22:13" />having_come to me and having_stood_by, he_said to_me: Saulos, brother, receive_sight. And_I looked_up on him to_ the _same hour. <verse eid="ACT 22:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 22:14" />And he said: The <char style="nd">god</char> of_the fathers of_us appointed you to_know the will of_him, and to_see the righteous <char style="add">&gt;one</char>, and to_hear <char style="add">+the</char>_voice out_of the mouth of_him. <verse eid="ACT 22:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 22:15" />Because you_will_be <char style="add">+a</char>_witness for_him to all people, of_what <char style="add">&gt;things</char> you_have_seen and heard. <verse eid="ACT 22:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 22:16" />And now why are_you_waiting? Having_risen_up, immerse and wash_away the sins of_you, having_appealed to_the name of_him. <verse eid="ACT 22:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 22:17" />And it_became to_me, having_returned to Hierousalaʸm, and praying of_me in the temple, me to_become in <char style="add">+a</char>_trance, <verse eid="ACT 22:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 22:18" />and to_see him saying to_me: Hurry and come_out with quickness out_of Hierousalaʸm, because they will_ not _be_accepting of_you <char style="add">+the</char>_testimony concerning me. <verse eid="ACT 22:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 22:19" />And_I said: <char style="nd">master</char>, they are_knowing that I was imprisoning and beating in the synagogues, the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> believing in you. <verse eid="ACT 22:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 22:20" />And when the blood of_Stefanos the witness of_you, was_being_poured_out, I_ myself _was also having_stood_by, and consenting, and keeping the clothes of_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> killing him. <verse eid="ACT 22:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 22:21" />And he_said to me: Be_going, because I will_be_sending_ you _away to far pagans. <verse eid="ACT 22:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 22:22" />And they_were_hearing from_him until this message, and they_lifted_up the voice of_them saying: Be_taking_away such <char style="add">man</char> from the earth, for it_was_ not _befitting him to_be_living. <verse eid="ACT 22:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 22:23" />and them Crying_out, and throwing_down their clothes, and throwing dust into the air, <verse eid="ACT 22:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 22:24" />the commander commanded him to_be_being_brought_in into the barracks, having_said him to_be_being_interrogated by_floggings, in_order_that he_may_know for what cause they_were_crying_out thus to_him. <verse eid="ACT 22:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 22:25" />But as they_stretched_ him _out with_the straps, Paulos said to the centurion having_stood, is_it_permitting to_you_all to_be_flogging <char style="add">+a</char>_man Ɽōmaios and uncondemned? <verse eid="ACT 22:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 22:26" />And having_heard <char style="add">it</char> the centurion, having_approached to_the commander, he_reported saying: What are_you_going to_be_doing? For this man is <char style="add">+a</char>_Ɽōmaios. <verse eid="ACT 22:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 22:27" />And having_approached, the commander said to_him: Be_telling to_me, are you <char style="add">+a</char>_Ɽōmaios? And he was_saying: Yes. <verse eid="ACT 22:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 22:28" />and the commander answered: I this acquired citizenship of_<char style="add">+a</char>_great sum. But Paulos was_saying: But I even have_been_born <char style="add">free</char>. <verse eid="ACT 22:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 22:29" />Therefore the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> going to_be_interrogating him immediately withdrew from him, the also and was_ commander _afraid, having_learned that he_is <char style="add">+a</char>_Ɽōmaios, and because he_was having_bound him. <verse eid="ACT 22:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 22:30" />But on_the <char style="add">day</char> of_next, wishing to_know for_certain, why he_is_being_accused by the Youdaiōns, he_released him, and commanded the chief_priests and all the council, to_come_together, and having_brought_down Paulos, he_set <char style="add"> him</char> among them.<chapter eid="ACT 22" /><chapter number="23" style="c" sid="ACT 23" /><verse eid="ACT 22:30" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 23:1" />And Paulos having_looked_intently at_the council said: Men, brothers, I in_all conscience have_lived_as_citizen good to_<char style="nd">god</char> until this day. <verse eid="ACT 23:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 23:2" />And Ananias the chief_priest commanded to_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_stood_by him, to_be_striking the mouth of_him. <verse eid="ACT 23:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 23:3" />Then Paulos said to him: <char style="nd">god</char> is_going to_be_striking you, wall having_been_whitewashed. And are_ you _sitting judging me according_to the law, and you_are_ violating_law _commanding me to_be_being_struck? <verse eid="ACT 23:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 23:4" />But the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_stood_by said: Are_you_insulting the chief_priest of_<char style="nd">god</char>? <verse eid="ACT 23:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 23:5" />And Paulos was_saying: I_had_ not _known, brothers, that he_is <char style="add">+a</char>_chief_priest, for it_has_been_written, you will_ not _be_speaking wrongly <char style="add">+A</char>_ruler of_the people of_you. <verse eid="ACT 23:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 23:6" />But Paulos having_known that one part is of_Saddoukaios_<char style="add">sect</char>, but the <char style="add">+the</char>_other of_Farisaios_<char style="add">party</char>, he_was_crying_out in the council: Men, brothers, I am <char style="add">+a</char>_Farisaios_<char style="add">party_member</char>, <char style="add">+the</char>_son of_Farisaios_<char style="add">party</char>, I am_being_judged concerning <char style="add">+the</char>_hope and resurrection of_<char style="add">+the</char>_dead. <verse eid="ACT 23:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 23:7" />And of_him speaking this, <char style="add">+a</char>_dissension became ˱between˲_the Farisaios_<char style="add">party</char> and Saddoukaios_<char style="add">sect</char>, and the multitude was_divided. <verse eid="ACT 23:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 23:8" />For indeed <char style="add">+the</char>_Saddoukaios_<char style="add">sect</char> are_saying to_be no resurrection, neither <char style="add">+an</char>_angel, nor <char style="add">+a</char>_spirit, But <char style="add">+the</char>_Farisaios_<char style="add">party</char> are_confessing both. <verse eid="ACT 23:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 23:9" />And <char style="add">+a</char>_ great _clamour became, and some of_the scribes of_the side of_the Farisaios_<char style="add">party</char> having_stood_up, they_were_contending saying: We_are_finding nothing evil in this man, and <char style="add">what</char> if <char style="add">+a</char>_spirit spoke to_him, or <char style="add">+an</char>_angel? <verse eid="ACT 23:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 23:10" />And becoming great, dissension, the commander having_been_afraid lest Paulos may_be_torn_apart by them, commanded the army having_come_downhill, to_snatch him from midst of_them, and to_be_bringing <char style="add"> him</char> into the barracks. <verse eid="ACT 23:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 23:11" />But on_the following night, the <char style="nd">master</char> having_approached to_him, said: Be_having_courage, for as you_testified the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> about me at Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim), thus it_is_fitting you to_testify also at Ɽōmaʸ. <verse eid="ACT 23:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 23:12" />And it_having_become day, the Youdaiōns having_made <char style="add">+a</char>_disorderly_gathering, cursed themselves, saying neither to_eat nor to_drink, until of_which they_may_kill_off Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 23:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 23:13" />And were more <char style="add">=than</char> forty the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> in_this having_made conspiracy, <verse eid="ACT 23:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 23:14" />who having_approached to_the chief_priests and the elders said: ˱With˲_<char style="add">+a</char>_curse we_cursed ourselves, to_taste of_nothing until of_which we_may_kill_off Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 23:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 23:15" />Therefore now you_all with the council report to_the commander, so_that he_may_bring_ him _down to you_all, as going to_be_investigating more_exactly the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning him, and we are ready to_kill him before the <char style="add">time</char> him to_near, . <verse eid="ACT 23:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 23:16" />But the son of_the sister of_Paulos having_heard, the ambush having_arrived, and having_come_in into the barracks, he_reported <char style="add">it</char> to_Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 23:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 23:17" />And Paulos having_called_to one of_the centurions, he_was_saying, be_bringing_up this young_man to the commander, for he_is_having something to_report to_him. <verse eid="ACT 23:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 23:18" />Therefore indeed the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> having_taken him, brought <char style="add"> him</char> to the commander, and he_is_saying: The prisoner, Paulos, having_called_to me, asked to_lead this young_man to you, having something to_tell to_you. <verse eid="ACT 23:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 23:19" />And the commander having_taken_hold of_the hand of_him, and having_withdrawn by himself, he_was_inquiring: What is <char style="add">it</char> that you_are_having to_report to_me? <verse eid="ACT 23:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 23:20" />And he_said, The Youdaiōns decided to_ask you, so_that tomorrow you_may_bring_down Paulos into the council, as going to_be_inquiring something more_exactly concerning him. <verse eid="ACT 23:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 23:21" />Therefore you may_ not _be_persuaded by_them, for forty of them men <char style="add">=than</char> more are_lying_in_wait him, who cursed themselves neither to_eat nor to_drink, until of_which they_may_kill him, and now they_are ready, waiting_for the promise from you. <verse eid="ACT 23:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 23:22" />Therefore indeed the commander sent_away the young_man having_commanded: To_tell to_no_one that you_reported these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> to me. <verse eid="ACT 23:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 23:23" />And having_called_to some two of_the centurions, he_said: Prepare two_hundred soldiers, so_that may_be_gone as_far_as Kaisareia, and seventy horsemen, and two_hundred spearmen for <char style="add">+the</char>_third hour of_the night. <verse eid="ACT 23:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 23:24" />And mounts to_present, in_order_that having_mounted Paulos, they_may_bring_safely_through <char style="add"> him</char> to Faʸlix the governor, <verse eid="ACT 23:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 23:25" />having_written <char style="add">+a</char>_letter, having this pattern: <verse eid="ACT 23:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 23:26" />Klaudios Lusias, to_be_greeting to_the most_excellent governor Faʸlix. <verse eid="ACT 23:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 23:27" />this man having_been_captured by the Youdaiōns, and going to_be_being_killed by them, having_approached with their army, I_rescued <char style="add"> him</char> having_learned that he_is <char style="add">+a</char>_Ɽōmaios. <verse eid="ACT 23:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 23:28" />And wishing to_know the charge because_of which they_were_indicting against_him, I_brought_down <char style="add"> him</char> to the council of_them. <verse eid="ACT 23:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 23:29" />Whom I_found being_indicted concerning questions of_the law of_them, but nothing having indictment worthy of_death or of_bonds. <verse eid="ACT 23:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 23:30" />And having_been_divulged to_me of_<char style="add">+a</char>_plot going_to_be against the man, I_sent <char style="add"> him</char> from them to you, having_ also _commanded to_the accusers them to_be_speaking before you. <verse eid="ACT 23:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 23:31" />Therefore indeed the soldiers according_to the <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> having_been_directed to_them, having_taken_up Paulos, brought <char style="add"> him</char> by night to Antipatris. <verse eid="ACT 23:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 23:32" />But on_the <char style="add">day</char> of_ next, having_allowed the horsemen to_be_going_away with him, they_returned to the barracks, <verse eid="ACT 23:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 23:33" />who having_come_in into Kaisareia, and having_delivered_up the letter to_the governor, they_ also _presented Paulos to_him. <verse eid="ACT 23:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 23:34" />And having_read <char style="add">it</char>, and having_asked of what province he_is, and having_learned that <char style="add">he_is</char> from Kilikia, <verse eid="ACT 23:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 23:35" />he_was_saying I_will_be_thoroughly_hearing from_you: whenever also the accusers of_you may_arrive, having_commanded for_him to_be_being_guarded in the residence_of_the_governor of_Haʸrōdaʸs.<chapter eid="ACT 23" /><chapter number="24" style="c" sid="ACT 24" /><verse eid="ACT 23:35" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 24:1" />And after five days, Ananias the chief_priest came_downhill with some elders, and Tertullos <char style="add">+a</char>_certain <char style="add">+an</char>_attorney, who reported to_the governor against Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 24:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 24:2" />And of_him having_been_called, Tertullos began to_be_accusing <char style="add"> him</char> saying: Of_great peace obtaining through you, and of_<char style="add">+the</char>_reforms becoming to_ this _nation through your provision, <verse eid="ACT 24:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 24:3" />both everything and everywhere, most_excellent Faʸlix we_are_welcoming <char style="add">it</char>, with all thanksgiving. <verse eid="ACT 24:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 24:4" />But in_order_that I _may_ not _be_hindering more for you, in_your gentleness I_am_imploring you to_hear from_us briefly. <verse eid="ACT 24:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 24:5" />For having_found this man <char style="add">+a</char>_pestilence, and stirring insurrections to_all the Youdaiōns in the inhabited_world, and <char style="add">+a</char>_ring_leader of_the of_the Nazōraios sect, <verse eid="ACT 24:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 24:6" />who even attempted to_profane the temple, also whom we_apprehended. <verse eid="ACT 24:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 24:7" /><verse eid="ACT 24:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 24:8" />from whom you_will_be_able yourself, having_examined <char style="add"> him</char> concerning all these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, to_know of_which <char style="add">&gt;things</char> we are_accusing against_him. <verse eid="ACT 24:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 24:9" />And the Youdaiōns also piled_on, alleging these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> to_be_having thus. <verse eid="ACT 24:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 24:10" />And Paulos answered, the governor having_nodded to_him to_be_speaking, this for many years you being judge to_nation Knowing, I_am_ cheerfully _defending the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning myself. <verse eid="ACT 24:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 24:11" />Of_you being_able to_know that there_are not more to_me twelve days, from which I_went_uphill going_to_prostrate in Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim). <verse eid="ACT 24:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 24:12" />And they_found me neither in the temple discussing with anyone or making <char style="add">+a</char>_opposition of_<char style="add">+a</char>_crowd, neither in the synagogues, nor in the city, <verse eid="ACT 24:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 24:13" />nor are_they_being_able to_stand_by to_you, concerning which now they_are_accusing against_me. <verse eid="ACT 24:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 24:14" />But I_am_confessing this to_you that according_to the way which they_are_calling <char style="add">+a</char>_sect, thus I_am_serving unto_the ancestral <char style="nd">god</char>, believing in_all the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> throughout the law and in_the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> having_been_written in the prophets, <verse eid="ACT 24:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 24:15" />having <char style="add">+a</char>_hope in <char style="nd">god</char>, which also these themselves are_waiting_for, <char style="add">+a</char>_resurrection to_be_going going_to_be, of_<char style="add">+the</char>_righteous both and of_<char style="add">+the</char>_unrighteous. <verse eid="ACT 24:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 24:16" />In this also I_ myself _am_exercising, <char style="add">+a</char>_ inoffensive _conscience to_be_having toward <char style="nd">god</char> and people through everything. <verse eid="ACT 24:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 24:17" />And through more years I_arrived going_to_make alms to the nation of_me and offerings, <verse eid="ACT 24:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 24:18" />at which they_found me in the temple having_been_purified, neither with <char style="add">+a</char>_crowd, nor with commotion. <verse eid="ACT 24:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 24:19" />But some Youdaiōns from Asia, who it_was_fitting to_be_being_present before you and to_be_accusing, if anything might_be_having against me. <verse eid="ACT 24:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 24:20" />Or let_ these themselves _say, what they_found wrong, having_stood of_me before the council, <verse eid="ACT 24:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 24:21" />than concerning this one voice, which I_cried_out among them having_stood: I am_being_judged by you_all today concerning <char style="add">+the</char>_resurrection of_<char style="add">+the</char>_dead. <verse eid="ACT 24:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 24:22" />But Faʸlix he_put_off them, having_known more_exactly the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning the way, having_said: Whenever Lusias the commander may_come_downhill, I_will_be_investigating the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning you_all, <verse eid="ACT 24:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 24:23" />having_directed to_the centurion him to_be_being_kept, and to_be_having relaxation, and to_be_forbidding no_one of_his own <char style="add">people</char> of_him to_be_attending to_him. <verse eid="ACT 24:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 24:24" />But after some days, Faʸlix having_arrived with Drousilla, his own wife being <char style="add">+a</char>_Youdaios, he_sent_for Paulos, and heard from_him concerning the faith in <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char>. <verse eid="ACT 24:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 24:25" />But him discussing concerning righteousness, and self-control, and the judgment coming, Faʸlix having_become frightened, answered: the_ Present _<char style="add">time</char> being be_going, and having_taken time, I_will_be_summoning you. <verse eid="ACT 24:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 24:26" />Together also hoping that money will_be_being_given to_him by Paulos, therefore also more_frequently sending_for him, he_was_conversing with_him. <verse eid="ACT 24:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 24:27" />But two_years having_been_fulfilled, Faʸlix received successor Porkios Faʸstos, and wanting to_grant <char style="add">+a</char>_favour to_the Youdaiōns, Faʸlix left Paulos having_been_bound.<chapter eid="ACT 24" /><chapter number="25" style="c" sid="ACT 25" /><verse eid="ACT 24:27" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 25:1" />Therefore Faʸstos having_set_foot_in in_the province after three, days went_uphill to Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim) from Kaisareia. <verse eid="ACT 25:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 25:2" />And the chief_priests and the leaders of_the Youdaiōns reported to_him against Paulos, and they_were_imploring him, <verse eid="ACT 25:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 25:3" />requesting <char style="add">+a</char>_favour against him, so_that he_may_send_for him to Hierousalaʸm (making <char style="add">+an</char>_ambush to_kill him on the way). <verse eid="ACT 25:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 25:4" />Therefore indeed Faʸstos answered, Paulos to_be_being_kept in Kaisareia, and himself to_be_going in quickness to_be_going_out. <verse eid="ACT 25:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 25:5" />Therefore the powerful <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> among you_all: he_is_saying, having_gone_down_with, if anything perverse is in the man, them _let_be_accusing against_him. <verse eid="ACT 25:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 25:6" />And having_stayed among them not more eight or ten days, having_come_downhill to Kaisareia, on_the <char style="add">day</char> of_next having_sat_down on the tribunal, he_commanded Paulos to_be_brought. <verse eid="ACT 25:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 25:7" />And of_him having_arrived, the Youdaiōns having_come_downhill from Hierousalaʸm stood_around him, bringing_against many and heavy charges, which they_were_ not _able to_demonstrate, <verse eid="ACT 25:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 25:8" />of_Paulos defending, I_sinned neither against the law of_the Youdaiōns, nor against the temple, nor anything against Kaisar. <verse eid="ACT 25:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 25:9" />But Faʸstos wanting to_grant favour with_the Youdaiōns, answering to_Paulos he_said: Are_you_willing to having_gone_up Hierousalaʸm concerning these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> to_be_judged there before me? <verse eid="ACT 25:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 25:10" />But Paulos said: Before the tribunal of_Kaisar having_stood I_am, where it_is_fitting me to_be_being_judged. I_have_done_ nothing _wrong To_<char style="add">+the</char>_Youdaiōns, as also you very_well are_knowing. <verse eid="ACT 25:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 25:11" />Therefore if on_one_hand I_am_doing_wrong and I_have_done anything worthy of_death, I_am_ not _refusing to_die_off, on_the_other_hand if nothing is <char style="add">true</char> of_which these are_accusing against_me, no_one is_able to_grant me to_them. I_am_Appealing to_Kaisar. <verse eid="ACT 25:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 25:12" />Then Faʸstos having_conversed_with with the counsel, answered: You_have_appealed to_Kaisar, you_will_be_going to Kaisar. <verse eid="ACT 25:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 25:13" />And some days having_elapsed, Agrippas the king and Bernikaʸ arrived to Kaisareia, having_greeted Faʸstos. <verse eid="ACT 25:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 25:14" />And as they_were_staying there more days, Faʸstos placed_before before_the king the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning Paulos saying, certain <char style="add">+a</char>_man ˱There˲_is, <char style="add">+a</char>_prisoner having_been_left by Faʸlix, <verse eid="ACT 25:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 25:15" />concerning whom of_me having_become in Hierousalaʸm, the chief_priests and the elders of_the Youdaiōns reported, requesting conviction against him, <verse eid="ACT 25:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 25:16" />to whom I_answered that it_is not <char style="add">+the</char>_custom with_Ɽōmaios to_be_granting any person before the <char style="add">&gt;one</char> being_accused, might_be_having to face the accusers and <char style="add">+the</char>_place of_defense might_take concerning the indictment. <verse eid="ACT 25:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 25:17" />Therefore of_them having_come_together, here, having_made not_one delay, on_the_ next _<char style="add">day</char> having_sat_down on the tribunal, I_commanded the man to_be_brought, <verse eid="ACT 25:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 25:18" />concerning whom the accusers having_been_stood they_were_bringing not_one charge, of_which I was_suspecting evil <char style="add">&gt;ones</char>. <verse eid="ACT 25:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 25:19" />But they_were_having against him some questions concerning their own superstition, and concerning <char style="add">+a</char>_certain <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> having_died, whom Paulos was_alleging to_be_living. <verse eid="ACT 25:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 25:20" />And I perplexing, the debate concerning these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, was_asking if might_be_wishing to_be_going to Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim), and_there to_be_being_judged concerning these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>. <verse eid="ACT 25:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 25:21" />But Paulos having_appealed to_be_kept himself for the investigation of_the Emperor, I_commanded him to_be_being_kept, until of_which I_may_send_ him _up to Kaisar. <verse eid="ACT 25:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 25:22" />And Agrippas <char style="add">said</char> to Faʸstos: I_was_wishing also myself to_hear from_the man. Tomorrow, he_is_saying: you_will_be_hearing from_him. <verse eid="ACT 25:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 25:23" />Therefore on_the <char style="add">day</char> of_next, Agrippas and Bernikaʸ having_come with great pageantry, and having_come_in into the auditorium with both commanders and men in prominence in_the city, and having_commanded Faʸstos, Paulos was_brought. <verse eid="ACT 25:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 25:24" />And Faʸstos is_saying: king Agrippas, and all you_all being_present_with with_us, men, you_all_are_observing this <char style="add">&gt;one</char>, concerning whom all the multitude of_the Youdaiōns pleaded with_me, in both Hierousalaʸm and here, shouting not to_be_fitting him to_be_living no_longer. <verse eid="ACT 25:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 25:25" />But I grasped him to_have_done nothing worthy of_death, and this <char style="add">&gt;one</char> himself having_appealed to_the Emperor, I_judged to_be_sending <char style="add"> him</char>. <verse eid="ACT 25:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 25:26" />Concerning whom I_am_ not _having any certain to_write to_my master. Therefore I_brought_ him _forth before you_all, and most_of_all before you, king Agrippas, so_that the examination having_become, I_may_have something I_may_write. <verse eid="ACT 25:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 25:27" />For it_is_supposing to_me illogical sending <char style="add">+a</char>_prisoner, not also to_signify the charges against him.<chapter eid="ACT 25" /><chapter number="26" style="c" sid="ACT 26" /><verse eid="ACT 25:27" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 26:1" />And Agrippas was_saying to Paulos: It_is_being_permitted to_you to_be_speaking concerning yourself. Then Paulos having_stretched_out his hand was_defending, <verse eid="ACT 26:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 26:2" />Concerning all of_which I_am_being_indicted by <char style="add">+the</char>_Youdaiōns, king Agrippas, I_have_considered myself blessed going to_be_defending before you, today. <verse eid="ACT 26:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 26:3" />Most_of_all you being knowledgeable_one of_all the among <char style="add">+the</char>_Youdaiōns, of_ both _customs and questions, therefore I_am_beseeching <char style="add">you</char> patiently to_hear from_me. <verse eid="ACT 26:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 26:4" />Therefore indeed the livelihood of_me, from youth from <char style="add">+the</char>_beginning having_become among the nation of_me and in Hierousalaʸm, all Youdaiōns have_known, <verse eid="ACT 26:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 26:5" />knowing_before me originally, if they_may_be_willing to_be_testifying that according_to the most_exact sect of_our religion, I_lived <char style="add">+a</char>_Farisaios_<char style="add">party_member</char>. <verse eid="ACT 26:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 26:6" />And now for <char style="add">+the</char>_hope of_the promise to the fathers of_us, having_become by <char style="nd">god</char>, I_have_stood being_judged, <verse eid="ACT 26:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 26:7" />to which the twelve_tribes of_us serving night and day in earnestness, is_hoping to_attain, concerning which <char style="add">+the</char>_hope I_am_being_indicted by <char style="add">+the</char>_Youdaiōns, king. <verse eid="ACT 26:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 26:8" />Why is_it_being_judged unbelievable by you_all, if <char style="nd">god</char> is_raising <char style="add">+the</char>_dead? <verse eid="ACT 26:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 26:9" />Therefore indeed I supposed to_myself it_to_be_fitting to_do many contrary <char style="add">&gt;things</char> to the name of_<char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char> of_from_Nazaret. <verse eid="ACT 26:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 26:10" />Which also I_did in Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim), and many both of_the holy <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> I locked_up in prisons, having_received the authority from the chief_priests, and of_them being_killed, I_brought_ <char style="add">+a</char>_vote _against <char style="add">them</char>. <verse eid="ACT 26:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 26:11" />And in all the synagogues, often punishing them, I_was_compelling <char style="add">them</char> to_be_slandering, and exceedingly raging_against against_them, I_was_persecuting <char style="add">them</char> as_far_as even to the outside cities. <verse eid="ACT 26:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 26:12" />At which journeying to Damaskos/(Dammeseq), with <char style="add">+the</char>_authority and permission of_the chief_priests, <verse eid="ACT 26:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 26:13" />middle day on the road king I_saw, from_heaven <char style="add">+a</char>_light above the brightness <char style="add">like</char> of_the sun having_shone_around me, and the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> journeying with me. <verse eid="ACT 26:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 26:14" />And all of_us having_falling_down to the ground, I_heard <char style="add">+a</char>_voice, saying to me in_the Hebraios language: Saulos/(Shāʼūl), Saulos, why are_you_persecuting me? <char style="add">It_is</char> hard for_you to_be_kicking against <char style="add">+the</char>_prods. <verse eid="ACT 26:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 26:15" />And I said: Who you_are, master? And the <char style="nd">master</char> said: I am <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char>, whom you are_persecuting. <verse eid="ACT 26:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 26:16" />But rise_up, and stand on the feet of_you, for I_was_seen by_you in this, to_appoint you <char style="add">+a</char>_attendant and <char style="add">+a</char>_witness, both of_which you_saw me and of_which I_will_be_being_seen by_you, <verse eid="ACT 26:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 26:17" />rescuing you from the people and from the pagans, to whom I am_sending_ you _out, <verse eid="ACT 26:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 26:18" />to_open_up eyes of_them, for_that to_turn_back from darkness to light, and from_the power of_Satan/(Sāţān) to <char style="nd">god</char>, for_that them to_receive forgiveness of_sins and lot among the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> having_been_sanctified by_faith in me. <verse eid="ACT 26:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 26:19" />Whence, king Agrippas, I_became not unpersuadable to_the heavenly vision, <verse eid="ACT 26:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 26:20" />but to_the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> in Damaskos first and both, in_Hierousalaʸm, and all the region of_Youdaia, and to_the pagans, I_was_reporting to_be_repenting and to_be_turning_back to <char style="nd">god</char>, worthy of_ works _repentance doing. <verse eid="ACT 26:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 26:21" />On_account these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, <char style="add">+the</char>_Youdaiōns having_captured me in the temple, were_attempting to_hand_over <char style="add">me</char>. <verse eid="ACT 26:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 26:22" />Therefore having_obtained of_help from <char style="nd">god</char> until this day, I_have_stood testifying to_small both and to_great, nothing besides saying of_what <char style="add">&gt;things</char> both the prophets and Mōsaʸs/(Mosheh) spoke going to_be_becoming, <verse eid="ACT 26:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 26:23" />the <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char> if suffering, if first by resurrection from_<char style="add">+the</char>_dead, is_going to_be_proclaiming light both to_<char style="add">+the</char>_people and the pagans. <verse eid="ACT 26:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 26:24" />And of_him defending these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, Faʸstos with_loud voice is_saying: You_are_raving_mad, Paulos. The great learning is_turning you to madness. <verse eid="ACT 26:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 26:25" />But Paulos: Is_saying I_am_ not _raving_mad: most_excellent Faʸstos, but I_am_speaking_out messages of_truth and sobriety. <verse eid="ACT 26:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 26:26" />For the king is_understanding concerning these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, to whom I_am_ also _speaking speaking_boldly, for I_am_being_persuaded nothing to_be_escaping_notice him anything of_these <char style="add">&gt;things</char> not, for this is not having_been_done in <char style="add">+a</char>_corner. <verse eid="ACT 26:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 26:27" />king Agrippas are_you_believing, in_the prophets? I_have_known that you_are_believing. <verse eid="ACT 26:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 26:28" />And Agrippas <char style="add">said</char> to Paulos: Are_you_persuading me in <char style="add">+a</char>_little <char style="add">time</char> to_make <char style="add">+a</char>_follower_of_the_messiah? <verse eid="ACT 26:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 26:29" />And Paulos <char style="add">said</char>: I_might_hope to_<char style="nd">god</char>, both in <char style="add">+a</char>_little <char style="add">time</char> and in <char style="add">+a</char>_great <char style="add">time</char>, not only you, but also all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> hearing from_me today, to_become such what_kind also_I am, except of_ these _bonds. <verse eid="ACT 26:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 26:30" />both the king and the governor Stood_up, both Bernikaʸ and the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> sitting_with with_them, <verse eid="ACT 26:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 26:31" />and having_withdrawn they_were_speaking to one_another saying, This man any not_one worthy <char style="add">&gt;thing</char> of_death or of_bonds is_doing. <verse eid="ACT 26:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 26:32" />And Agrippas was_saying to_Faʸstos: This man was_able to_have_sent_away, except he_had_appealed Kaisar.<chapter eid="ACT 26" /><chapter number="27" style="c" sid="ACT 27" /><verse eid="ACT 26:32" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 27:1" />And when it_was_judged us to_be_sailing_away to Italia, they_were_giving_over both Paulos and some other prisoners, to_<char style="add">+a</char>_centurion by_<char style="add">+the</char>_name Youlios, of_<char style="add">+the</char>_cohort of_Augustus/(Sebastos). <verse eid="ACT 27:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 27:2" />And having_boarded on_<char style="add">+a</char>_ Adramuttaʸnos _ship, we_were_launched going to_be_sailing to the places along Asia, of_Aristarⱪos being with us, <char style="add">+a</char>_from_Makedonia of_from_Thessalonikaʸ. <verse eid="ACT 27:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 27:3" />Both on_the next <char style="add">day</char> we_were_set_down at Sidōn/(Tsīdōn), and Youlios having_given_treatment with_human_kindness to_Paulos, he_permitted <char style="add"> him</char> having_been_gone to his friends, to_obtain of_care. <verse eid="ACT 27:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 27:4" />And_from_there having_been_launched, we_sailed_under Kupros, because_of that the winds to_be contrary. <verse eid="ACT 27:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 27:5" />And having_sailed_astake the sea along Kilikia and Pamfulia, we_came_downhill to Mura of_Lukia. <verse eid="ACT 27:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 27:6" />And_there the centurion having_found <char style="add">+a</char>_ from_Alexandria _ship, sailing to Italia, he_placed_in us into it. <verse eid="ACT 27:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 27:7" />And in many days, slow_sailing and with_difficulty, having_become along Knidos, the wind not further_permitting us, we_sailed_under Kraʸtaʸ along Salmōn/(Saləmōn)e. <verse eid="ACT 27:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 27:8" />And sailing_along it with_difficulty, we_came to <char style="add">+a</char>_ certain _place being_called Beautiful Harbours, to_which was near <char style="add">+the</char>_city Lasaia. <verse eid="ACT 27:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 27:9" />And much time having_elapsed, and the voyage already being dangerous, because_of that even the fasting already to_have_passed_by, Paulos was_advising <char style="add">them</char> <verse eid="ACT 27:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 27:10" />saying to_them: Men, I_am_perceiving that the voyage to_be_going going_to_be with damage and much loss, not only of_the cargo and to_the ship, but also the lives of_us. <verse eid="ACT 27:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 27:11" />But the centurion was_being_persuaded by_the captain and the ship_owner rather, than by_the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> being_spoken by Paulos. <verse eid="ACT 27:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 27:12" />And the harbour being unsuitable to winter, the more presented <char style="add">+a</char>_counsel to_be_launched from_there, if somehow they_might_be_able, having_arrived at Foinix, to_winter <char style="add">+a</char>_harbour of_Kraʸtaʸ, looking to <char style="add">+the</char>_southwest and to <char style="add">+the</char>_northwest. <verse eid="ACT 27:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 27:13" />And of_<char style="add">+a</char>_south_wind having_blown_gently, having_supposed of_the purpose to_have_taken_hold, having_taken_up they_were_sailing_along near Kraʸtaʸ. <verse eid="ACT 27:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 27:14" />But after not much <char style="add">time</char>, <char style="add">+a</char>_ typhoon _wind, being_called <char style="add">+the</char>_Eurokludōn throw down. from_it. <verse eid="ACT 27:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 27:15" />And the ship having_been_seized, and not being_able to_be_facing to_the wind, having_given_up we_were_being_driven_along. <verse eid="ACT 27:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 27:16" />And having_run_under <char style="add">+a</char>_certain island being_called Klaudaʸ, we_were_able with_difficulty to_become control of_the lifeboat, <verse eid="ACT 27:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 27:17" />which having_taken_up, they_were_resorting to_helps, undergirding the ship. And fearing lest they_may_run_aground into the <char style="add">shallows_of</char> Surtis, having_lowered the gear, thus they_were_being_driven_along. <verse eid="ACT 27:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 27:18" />And of_us being_ violently _storm_tossed, on_the_ next _<char style="add">day</char> they_were_making <char style="add">+a</char>_jettison, <verse eid="ACT 27:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 27:19" />and on_the third <char style="add">day</char>, they_threw_down the tackle of_the ship <char style="add">^their</char>_own_hands. <verse eid="ACT 27:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 27:20" />And neither sun nor stars appearing for more days, and no little storm laying_on <char style="add">us</char>, furthermore all hope, us to_be_being_saved was_being_taken_away. <verse eid="ACT 27:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 27:21" />And of_much abstinence being, then Paulos having_been_stood in midst of_them said: It_was_fitting indeed, oh men, having_yielded to_me, not to_be_being_launched from Kraʸtaʸ, and to_gain this damage, and the loss. <verse eid="ACT 27:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 27:22" />And_yet now I_am_advising you_all the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> to_be_cheering_up, for not_one loss of_life will_be of you_all, except of_the ship. <verse eid="ACT 27:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 27:23" />For <char style="add">+an</char>_angel of_<char style="nd">god</char> stood_by me this night, of_whose I_am, unto_whom also I_am_serving, <verse eid="ACT 27:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 27:24" />saying: Be_ not _fearing, Paulos, it_is_fitting you to_stand_before before_Kaisar, and see, <char style="nd">god</char> has_granted to_you all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> sailing with you. <verse eid="ACT 27:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 27:25" />Therefore be_cheering_up, men, for I_am_believing in_ <char style="nd">god</char> that thus it_will_be, according_to which manner it_has_been_spoken to_me. <verse eid="ACT 27:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 27:26" />But it_is_fitting us to_run_aground on <char style="add">+a</char>_certain island. <verse eid="ACT 27:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 27:27" />But when <char style="add">+the</char>_fourteenth night became, us being_carried_through in the Adrias_Sea, to <char style="add">+the</char>_middle of_the night, the sailors were_suspecting <char style="add">+a</char>_certain to_be_coming_near to_them land. <verse eid="ACT 27:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 27:28" />And having_taken_soundings, they_found twenty fathoms, and <char style="add">+a</char>_little <char style="add">time</char> having_passed_by, and again having_taken_soundings, they_found fifteen fathoms. <verse eid="ACT 27:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 27:29" />And fearing lest we_may_run_aground somewhere on rough places, having_thrown_down four anchors from <char style="add">+the</char>_stern, they_were_hoping for_day to_become. <verse eid="ACT 27:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 27:30" />And <char style="add">+the</char>_sailors seeking to_flee out_of the ship, and having_lowered the lifeboat into the sea, on_under_pretense as going to_be_stretching_out anchors from <char style="add">+the</char>_bow, <verse eid="ACT 27:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 27:31" />Paulos said to_the centurion and to_the soldiers: If these may_ not _remain in the ship, you_all are_ not _being_able to_be_saved. <verse eid="ACT 27:31" /><verse number="32" style="v" sid="ACT 27:32" />Then the soldiers cut_off the ropes of_the lifeboat, and they_allowed her to_run_aground. <verse eid="ACT 27:32" /><verse number="33" style="v" sid="ACT 27:33" />And until of_which day was_going to_be_becoming, Paulos was_exhorting all, to_partake of_food saying: Today <char style="add">+the</char>_fourteenth day <char style="add">=is</char>, you_all_are_continuing waiting foodless, having_taken nothing. <verse eid="ACT 27:33" /><verse number="34" style="v" sid="ACT 27:34" />Therefore I_am_exhorting you_all to_partake of_food, for this is_being for your salvation, for <char style="add">+a</char>_hair from the head of_no_one of_you_all will_be_perishing. <verse eid="ACT 27:34" /><verse number="35" style="v" sid="ACT 27:35" />And having_said these <char style="add">&gt;things</char>, and having_taken bread, he_gave_thanks to_<char style="nd">god</char> before all, and having_broke <char style="add">it</char>, he_began to_be_eating. <verse eid="ACT 27:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="ACT 27:36" />And all having_become cheerful, they also received of_food. <verse eid="ACT 27:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="ACT 27:37" />And we_were all souls in the ship, two_hundred seventy six. <verse eid="ACT 27:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="ACT 27:38" />And having_been_satiated of_food, they_were_lightening the ship, throwing_out the wheat into the sea. <verse eid="ACT 27:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="ACT 27:39" />And when day became, they_were_ not _recognizing the land, but were_observing <char style="add">+a</char>_certain bay having <char style="add">+a</char>_shore, on which they_were_counselling, if they_might_be_able to_preserve the ship. <verse eid="ACT 27:39" /><verse number="40" style="v" sid="ACT 27:40" />And having_cut_away the anchors, they_were_allowing <char style="add">them</char> in the sea, at_once having_unfastened the ropes of_the rudders, and having_lifted_up the foresail to_the <char style="add">wind</char> blowing, they_were_keeping for the shore. <verse eid="ACT 27:40" /><verse number="41" style="v" sid="ACT 27:41" />But having_fallen_among into <char style="add">+a</char>_place two_sea, they_ran_ the ship _aground, and on_one_hand the bow having_stuck remained unshakeable, on_the_other_hand the stern was_being_destroyed by the force. <verse eid="ACT 27:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="ACT 27:42" />And of_the soldiers, <char style="add">+the</char>_counsel became that they_may_kill_off the prisoners, lest anyone having_swum_away may_escape. <verse eid="ACT 27:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="ACT 27:43" />But the centurion wishing to_bring_ Paulos _safely_through, forbade them of_their counsel, and he_commanded the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being_able to_be_swimming, having_thrown_off <char style="add">themselves</char> first, to_be_departing on the land, <verse eid="ACT 27:43" /><verse number="44" style="v" sid="ACT 27:44" />and the rest, on_one_hand some on planks, on_the_other_hand some on some <char style="add">&gt;things</char> from the ship. And thus it_became, all to_be_brought_safely_through to the land.<chapter eid="ACT 27" /><chapter number="28" style="c" sid="ACT 28" /><verse eid="ACT 27:44" /><verse number="1" style="v" sid="ACT 28:1" />And having_been_brought_safely_through, then we_learned that the island is_being_called Melitaʸ. <verse eid="ACT 28:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ACT 28:2" />And the foreigners were_bringing_about not <char style="add">just</char> the having_been_ordinary human_kindness to_us, for having_lit <char style="add">+a</char>_fire, they_received all us, because_of the rain having_approached, and because_of the cold. <verse eid="ACT 28:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ACT 28:3" />But Paulos having_gathered some multitude of_sticks, and having_laid_on <char style="add">them</char> on the fire, <char style="add">+a</char>_viper having_come_out from the heat, clamped_down on_the hand of_him. <verse eid="ACT 28:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ACT 28:4" />And when the foreigners saw the wild_beast being_hanged from the hand of_him, they_were_saying to one_another: Certainly this man is <char style="add">+a</char>_murderer, whom having_been_brought_safely_through from the sea, justice not allowed <char style="add"> him</char> to_be_living. <verse eid="ACT 28:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ACT 28:5" />Therefore indeed he, having_shaken_off the wild_beast into the fire, suffered not_one harm. <verse eid="ACT 28:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ACT 28:6" />But they were_expecting him to_be_going to_be_being_swelled_up, or to_be_falling_down suddenly dead. But over much <char style="add">time</char>, them waiting and observing nothing amiss becoming to him, having_changed_their_minds they_were_saying him to_be <char style="add">+a</char>_god. <verse eid="ACT 28:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="ACT 28:7" />And in the <char style="add">parts</char> about that place, was_being properties to_the leader of_the island by_<char style="add">+the</char>_name Poplios, who having_accepted us hospitably lodged three days. <verse eid="ACT 28:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="ACT 28:8" />And it_became, the father of_Poplios to_be_lying_down being_gripped_with with_fevers and dysentery, to whom Paulos having_come_in, and having_prayed, having_laid_on the hands on_him, he_healed him. <verse eid="ACT 28:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="ACT 28:9" />And this having_become, also the rest in the island having sicknesses were_approaching and were_being_healed, <verse eid="ACT 28:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="ACT 28:10" />who also they_honoured us with_many honours, and being_launched, they_laid_on the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> for our needs. <verse eid="ACT 28:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="ACT 28:11" />And after three months, we_were_launched in <char style="add">+a</char>_ship having_wintered in the island, <char style="add">+an</char>_from_Alexandria with_<char style="add">+a</char>_figurehead to_Zeus_twins. <verse eid="ACT 28:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="ACT 28:12" />And having_been_set_down at Surakousai, we_remained_on three days, <verse eid="ACT 28:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="ACT 28:13" />whence having_cut_away, we_arrived at Ɽaʸgion. And after one day, having_come_on <char style="add">+a</char>_south_wind, <char style="add">+the</char>_second <char style="add">day</char> we_came to Potioloi, <verse eid="ACT 28:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ACT 28:14" />where having_found <char style="add">+the</char>_brothers, we_were_implored by them to_remain_on seven days. And thus we_came to Ɽōmaʸ. <verse eid="ACT 28:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ACT 28:15" />And_from_there the brothers having_heard, the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning us, came to meeting with_us until Appios Market and Three Taverns, whom Paulos having_seen, having_giving_thanks to_<char style="nd">god</char>, took courage. <verse eid="ACT 28:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="ACT 28:16" />And when we_came_in to Ɽōmaʸ, it_was_permitted to_Paulos to_be_remaining by himself, with the soldier guarding him. <verse eid="ACT 28:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="ACT 28:17" />And it_became after three days, him to_call_together the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> being leaders of_the Youdaiōns. And them having_come_together, he_was_saying to them: Men brothers I, having_done nothing contrary to_the people or the ancestral customs, <char style="add">+a</char>_prisoner from Hierousalaʸm/(Yərūshālayim) was_given_over into the hands of_the Ɽōmaios, <verse eid="ACT 28:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ACT 28:18" />who having_examined me, were_wishing to_send_away <char style="add">me</char>, because_of that not_one cause of_death to_be_being in me. <verse eid="ACT 28:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ACT 28:19" />But speaking_against of_the Youdaiōns, I_was_compelled to_appeal to_Kaisar, not as having anything to_be_accusing against_the nation of_me. <verse eid="ACT 28:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ACT 28:20" />Therefore for this cause, I_begged you_all, to_see and to_address, for on_account of_the hope of_Israaʸl/(Yisərāʼēl), this chain I_am_being_encompassed <char style="add">in</char>. <verse eid="ACT 28:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="ACT 28:21" />And they said to him: We neither received letters concerning you from Youdaia, nor having_arrived anyone of_the brothers reported or spoke anything evil concerning you. <verse eid="ACT 28:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ACT 28:22" />But we_are_considering_worthy to_hear from you what you_are_thinking, for indeed concerning this sect it_is known to_us, that it_is_being_spoken_against everywhere. <verse eid="ACT 28:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ACT 28:23" />And having_determined <char style="add">+a</char>_day for_him, more they_came to him to the lodging, to_whom he_was_explaining, testifying the kingdom of_<char style="nd">god</char>, and persuading them concerning <char style="nd">Yaʸsous/(Yəhōshūˊa)</char>, from both the law of_Mōsaʸs/(Mosheh), and the prophets, from in_the_morning to evening. <verse eid="ACT 28:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ACT 28:24" />And on_one_hand the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> were_being_persuaded by_the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> being_spoken, on_the_other_hand the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> were_disbelieving. <verse eid="ACT 28:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ACT 28:25" />And being discordant with one_another, they_were_sending_away, Paulos having_spoken one <char style="add">final</char> message: Rightly the holy <char style="nd">spirit</char> spoke by Aʸsaias/(Yəshaˊəyāh) the prophet to the fathers of_you_all <verse eid="ACT 28:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ACT 28:26" />saying: Be_gone to this people, and say: ˱In˲_hearing you_all_will_be_hearing, and by_no_means you_all_may_ not _understand, and seeing you_all_will_be_seeing, and by_no_means you_all_may_ not _perceive. <verse eid="ACT 28:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="ACT 28:27" />For the heart of_ this _people was_become_dull, and they_ hardly _heard with_their ears of_them, and they_shut the eyes of_them, lest they_may_see with_their eyes, and they_may_hear with_their ears, and they_may_understand with_their heart, and they_may_turn_back, and I_will_be_healing them. <verse eid="ACT 28:27" /><verse number="28" style="v" sid="ACT 28:28" />Therefore it_let_be known, to_you_all that this salvation of_<char style="nd">god</char> was_sent_out to_the pagans, and they will_be_hearing. <verse eid="ACT 28:28" /><verse number="29" style="v" sid="ACT 28:29" /><verse eid="ACT 28:29" /><verse number="30" style="v" sid="ACT 28:30" />And He_remained_in two_ whole _years in <char style="add">^his</char>_own rental, and was_welcoming all the <char style="add">&gt;ones</char> entering_in to him, <verse eid="ACT 28:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="ACT 28:31" />proclaiming the kingdom of_<char style="nd">god</char>, and unhinderedly teaching the <char style="add">&gt;things</char> concerning the <char style="nd">master</char> <char style="nd">Yaʸsous</char> <char style="nd">chosen_one/messiah</char>, with all boldness.<chapter eid="ACT 28" /></usx>